btl_state.dat
BTR_STATE_00_01	[~ 0]
BTR_STATE_00_02	[~ 1]
BTR_STATE_01_01	Harsh Sunlight
BTR_STATE_01_02	The harsh sunlight weather condition.\nIt boosts the power of Fire-type moves and\nlowers the power of Water-type moves.
BTR_STATE_02_01	Rain
BTR_STATE_02_02	The rain weather condition.\nIt boosts the power of Water-type moves and\nlowers the power of Fire-type moves.
BTR_STATE_03_01	Sandstorm
BTR_STATE_03_02	The sandstorm weather condition.\nAt the end of each turn, it damages all Pokémon\nthat are not Rock, Ground, or Steel type.\nIt boosts the Sp. Def of Rock-type Pokémon.
BTR_STATE_04_01	Hail
BTR_STATE_04_02	The hail weather condition.\nAt the end of each turn, it damages all Pokémon\nthat are not Ice type.
BTR_STATE_05_01	Electric Terrain
BTR_STATE_05_02	For five turns, Pokémon on the ground won’t\nfall asleep.\nThe power of Electric-type moves is boosted.
BTR_STATE_06_01	Grassy Terrain
BTR_STATE_06_02	For five turns, Pokémon on the ground will have\na little HP restored at the end of each turn.\nThe power of Grass-type moves is boosted.
BTR_STATE_07_01	Misty Terrain
BTR_STATE_07_02	For five turns, Pokémon on the ground won’t get\nany status conditions.\nDamage from Dragon-type moves is halved.
BTR_STATE_08_01	Trick Room
BTR_STATE_08_02	Slower Pokémon get to move first for five turns.
BTR_STATE_09_01	Magic Room
BTR_STATE_09_02	Pokémon can’t use their held items for five turns.
BTR_STATE_10_01	Wonder Room
BTR_STATE_10_02	Pokémon’s Defense and Sp. Def are swapped for\nfive turns.
BTR_STATE_11_01	Critical Hit Boost
BTR_STATE_11_02	The Pokémon is more likely to land critical hits.
BTR_STATE_12_01	Confusion
BTR_STATE_12_02	The Pokémon may hurt itself in its confusion.\nThe effect lasts for one to four turns.
BTR_STATE_13_01	Infatuation
BTR_STATE_13_02	The Pokémon is less likely to unleash an attack\non Pokémon of the opposite gender.
BTR_STATE_14_01	Nightmare
BTR_STATE_14_02	The Pokémon will lose HP each turn as long as\nit is sleeping.
BTR_STATE_15_01	Drowsy
BTR_STATE_15_02	The Pokémon will fall asleep at the end of the\nturn if it remains on the battlefield.
BTR_STATE_16_01	Encore
BTR_STATE_16_02	Due to Encore, the Pokémon can use only\n[VAR 0107(0000)] for three turns.
BTR_STATE_17_01	No Ability
BTR_STATE_17_02	The Pokémon’s Ability loses its effect.
BTR_STATE_18_01	Torment
BTR_STATE_18_02	The Pokémon can’t use the same move twice\nin a row.
BTR_STATE_19_01	Tailwind
BTR_STATE_19_02	The Speed stat of a Pokémon and its allies is\ndoubled for four turns.
BTR_STATE_20_01	Lucky Chant
BTR_STATE_20_02	The opponent’s moves won’t result in a\ncritical hit.
BTR_STATE_21_01	Grudge
BTR_STATE_21_02	If the Pokémon faints by an opponent’s move,\nthe PP of that move will be reduced to 0.
BTR_STATE_22_01	Heal Block
BTR_STATE_22_02	For five turns, the Pokémon is unable to recover\nHP through its moves, Ability, or held item.
BTR_STATE_23_01	Identified
BTR_STATE_23_02	The Pokémon will be hit by certain moves\nthat usually wouldn’t affect it.\nIf the Pokémon’s evasion has been boosted,\nthe benefits will be ignored when it is attacked.
BTR_STATE_24_01	Disable
BTR_STATE_24_02	For four turns, the Pokémon will be unable to\nuse [VAR 0107(0000)].
BTR_STATE_25_01	Can’t Escape
BTR_STATE_25_02	The Pokémon can’t flee or be switched out.
BTR_STATE_26_01	Lock-On
BTR_STATE_26_02	The next move used by the Pokémon will be sure\nto hit the target.
BTR_STATE_27_01	Embargo
BTR_STATE_27_02	For five turns, the Pokémon cannot use its held\nitem and no items can be used on it.
BTR_STATE_28_01	Charge
BTR_STATE_28_02	The power of an Electric-type move will be\ndoubled if used in the turn after charging.
BTR_STATE_29_01	Gravity
BTR_STATE_29_02	Moves are more likely to hit for five turns.\nGround-type moves will hit Flying-type\nPokémon and Pokémon with the Levitate Ability.\nMoves that require action midair can’t be used.
BTR_STATE_30_01	Mist
BTR_STATE_30_02	The Pokémon’s stats won’t be lowered for\nfive turns.
BTR_STATE_31_01	Safeguard
BTR_STATE_31_02	The Pokémon is protected from status conditions\nfor five turns.
BTR_STATE_32_01	Stealth Rock
BTR_STATE_32_02	Pokémon that switch into battle will\ntake damage.
BTR_STATE_33_01	Stockpile
BTR_STATE_33_02	The Pokémon’s Defense and Sp. Def stats\ngo up while stockpiling.
BTR_STATE_34_01	Taunt
BTR_STATE_34_02	The Pokémon can only use moves that\ndeal damage.
BTR_STATE_35_01	Telekinesis

WAZAINFO_707	Driven by frustration, the user attacks the target. If\nthe user’s previous move has failed, the power of\nthis move doubles.
WAZAINFO_708	The user attacks by beating the target with a\nbone that contains a spirit. This may also lower\nthe target’s Defense stat.
WAZAINFO_709	The user smashes into the target at high speed.\nThis move always goes first.
WAZAINFO_710	The user slams into the target using a full-force\nblast of water. This may also lower the target’s\nDefense stat.
WAZAINFO_711	The user shoots powerful lasers using the power of\na prism. The user can’t move on the next turn.
WAZAINFO_712	The user hides in the target’s shadow, steals\nthe target’s stat boosts, and then attacks.
WAZAINFO_713	The user slams into the target with the force of a\nmeteor. This move can be used on the target\nregardless of its Abilities.
WAZAINFO_714	The user emits a sinister ray to attack the target.\nThis move can be used on the target regardless of\nits Abilities.
WAZAINFO_715	The user gets teary eyed to make the target lose\nits combative spirit. This lowers the target’s\nAttack and Sp. Atk stats.
WAZAINFO_716	A strong electric blast crashes down on the target,\ngiving it an electric shock. This may also make the\ntarget flinch.
WAZAINFO_717	The user hits the target with the force of nature.\nIt halves the target’s HP.
WAZAINFO_718	Cloaking itself in high energy, the user slams into the\ntarget. The memory held determines the move’s type.
WAZAINFO_719	The user, Pikachu wearing a cap, powers up a jolt of\nelectricity using its Z-Power and unleashes it.\nCritical hits land more easily.
WAZAINFO_720	The user attacks everything around it by causing its\nown head to explode. This also damages the user.
WAZAINFO_721	The user attacks with electrically charged fists.\nThis move changes Normal-type moves to\nElectric-type moves.
WAZAINFO_722	The user attacks a target with a pillar of light. This\nmove inflicts Attack or Sp. Atk damage—whichever\nstat is higher for the user.
WAZAINFO_723	This attack inflicts Attack or Sp. Atk damage—\nwhichever stat is higher for the user, Necrozma.\nThis move ignores the target’s Ability.
WAZAINFO_724	After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Solgaleo,\nattacks the target with full force. This move can\nignore the effect of the target’s Ability.
WAZAINFO_725	After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Lunala,\nattacks the target with full force. This move can\nignore the effect of the target’s Ability.
WAZAINFO_726	After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Mimikyu,\npunches the target with full force.
WAZAINFO_727	After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Lycanroc,\nattacks the target with full force. This move negates\nthe effect on the battlefield.
WAZAINFO_728	After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Kommo-o,\nattacks the opposing Pokémon with full force. This\nmove boosts the user’s stats.
WAZAINFO_729	The user attacks the target with bursts of electricity\nat high speed. This move always goes first and results\nin a critical hit.
WAZAINFO_730	The user charges a huge wave with electricity and\nhits the opposing Pokémon with the wave. This may\nalso leave the opposing Pokémon with paralysis.
WAZAINFO_731	The user floats in the air, and then dives at a steep\nangle to attack the target. This may also make the\ntarget flinch.
WAZAINFO_732	The more Pikachu loves its Trainer, the greater the\nmove’s power. It never misses.
WAZAINFO_733	The user attacks by shooting water bubbles at the\ntarget. It then absorbs water and restores its HP by half\nthe damage taken by the target.
WAZAINFO_734	The user shoots a jolt of electricity to attack the target.\nThis also leaves the target with paralysis.
WAZAINFO_735	The user cloaks itself in fire and charges at the target.\nThis also leaves the target with a burn.
WAZAINFO_736	The user bombards the target with telekinetic force.\nA wondrous wall of light is put up to weaken the power\nof the opposing Pokémon’s special moves.
WAZAINFO_737	The user acts bad and attacks the target.\nA wondrous wall of light is put up to weaken the power\nof the opposing Pokémon’s physical moves.
WAZAINFO_738	The user grows a gigantic stalk that scatters seeds\nto attack the target. The seeds drain the target’s\nHP every turn.
WAZAINFO_739	The user attacks with a crystal made of cold frozen\nhaze. It eliminates every stat change among all the\nPokémon engaged in battle.

WAZAINFO_741	The more Eevee loves its Trainer, the greater the\nmove’s power. It never misses.
WAZAINFO_742	The user rotates, centering the hex nut in its chest,\nand then strikes with its arms twice in a row. This may\nalso make the target flinch.

ZKN_COMMENT_A_000_000	
ZKN_COMMENT_A_001_000	It can go for days without eating a single morsel.\nIn the bulb on its back, it stores energy.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_002_000	The bud on its back grows by drawing energy. It\ngives off an aroma when it is ready to bloom.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_003_000	The flower on its back catches the sun’s rays.\nThe sunlight is then absorbed and\nused for energy.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_004_000	The flame at the tip of its tail makes a sound as\nit burns. You can only hear it in quiet places.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_005_000	Tough fights could excite this Pokémon. When\nexcited, it may breathe out bluish-white flames.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_006_000	When this Pokémon expels a blast of superhot\nfire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns\nmore intensely.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_007_000	Shoots water at prey while in the water.\nWithdraws into its shell when in danger.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_008_000	When tapped on its head, this Pokémon will pull\nit in, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_009_000	Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out\nwater with even more force than a fire hose.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_010_000	If you touch the feeler on top of its head, it will\nrelease a horrible stink to protect itself.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_011_000	Hardens its shell to protect itself. However, a\nlarge impact may cause it to pop out of its shell.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_012_000	Its wings, covered with poisonous powder, repel\nwater. This allows it to fly in the rain.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_013_000	Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides\nin grass and bushes where it eats leaves.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_014_000	Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it\nmay stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_015_000	It has three poisonous stingers on its\nforelegs and its tail. They are used to jab\nits enemy repeatedly.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_016_000	Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up\nsand to protect itself rather than fight back.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_017_000	This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies\naround its large territory in search of prey.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_018_000	This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed,\nseeking prey. Its large talons are feared\nas wicked weapons.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_019_000	Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you\nsee one, you can be certain that 40 more\nlive in the area.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_020_000	Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers,\nso it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_021_000	Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around\nvery fast to protect its territory.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_022_000	A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it\nsenses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_023_000	The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it\nwraps its long body around tree branches to rest.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_024_000	The frightening patterns on its belly have been\nstudied. Six variations have been confirmed.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_025_000	This forest-dwelling Pokémon stores electricity\nin its cheeks, so you’ll feel a tingly shock\nif you touch it.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_026_000	When electricity builds up inside its body, it\nbecomes feisty. It also glows in the dark.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_027_000	Its body is dry. When it gets cold at night, its\nhide is said to become coated with a fine dew.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_028_000	It is skilled at slashing enemies with its claws.\nIf broken, they start to grow back in a day.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_029_000	A mild-mannered Pokémon that does not like\nto fight. Beware—its small horn secretes venom.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_030_000	When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always\nretract. This is proof that it is relaxed.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_031_000	Tough scales cover the sturdy body of\nthis Pokémon. It appears that the scales\ngrow in cycles.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_032_000	Its large ears are always kept upright. If it senses\ndanger, it will attack with a poisonous sting.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_033_000	Its horn contains venom. If it stabs an\nenemy with the horn, the impact makes\nthe poison leak out.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_034_000	Its steel-like hide adds to its powerful tackle.\nIts horns are so hard, they can pierce a diamond.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_035_000	Adored for their cute looks and playfulness.\nThey are thought to be rare, as they\ndo not appear often.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_036_000	They appear to be very protective of their own\nworld. It is a kind of fairy, rarely seen by people.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_037_000	Both its fur and its tails are beautiful.\nAs it grows, the tails split and form more tails.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_038_000	According to an enduring legend, nine noble\nsaints were united and reincarnated\nas this Pokémon.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_039_000	Uses its cute round eyes to enrapture its foe.\nIt then sings a pleasing melody that lulls\nthe foe to sleep.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_040_000	Its body is very elastic. By inhaling deeply,\nit can continue to inflate itself without limit.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_041_000	Emits ultrasonic cries while it flies. They act as\na sonar used to check for objects in its way.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_042_000	It attacks in a stealthy manner,\nwithout warning. Its sharp fangs\nare used to bite and to suck blood.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_043_000	It may be mistaken for a clump of weeds.\nIf you try to yank it out of the ground,\nit shrieks horribly.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_044_000	Smells incredibly foul! However, around one\nout of a thousand people enjoy sniffing\nits nose-bending stink.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_045_000	Flaps its broad flower petals to scatter\nits poisonous pollen. The flapping sound\nis very loud.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_046_000	Burrows under the ground to gnaw on\ntree roots. The mushrooms on its back\nabsorb most of the nutrition.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_047_000	The bug host is drained of energy by\nthe mushroom on its back. The mushroom\nappears to do all the thinking.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_048_000	Its large eyes act as radar. In a bright place, you\ncan see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_049_000	The powdery scales on its wings are hard to\nremove from skin. They also contain poison\nthat leaks out on contact.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_050_000	It prefers dark places. It spends most of its time\nunderground, though it may pop up in caves.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_051_000	A team of triplets that can burrow to a depth\nof 60 miles. It’s reported that this triggers\nan earthquake.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_052_000	Appears to be more active at night. It loves\nround and shiny things. It can’t stop itself from\npicking them up.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_053_000	The gem in its forehead glows on its own!\nIt walks with all the grace and elegance\nof a proud queen.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_054_000	Always tormented by headaches. It uses\npsychic powers, but whether it intends to\ndo so is not known.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_055_000	Its long, slim limbs end in broad flippers.\nThey are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_056_000	An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers\neasily and will not hesitate to attack anything.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_057_000	It stops being angry only when nobody else\nis around. To view this moment is very difficult.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_058_000	A Pokémon with a friendly nature.\nHowever, it will bark fiercely at\nanything invading its territory.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_059_000	A legendary Pokémon in the East. Many people\nare charmed by the grace and beauty of\nits running.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_060_000	The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by\narea. It is more adept at swimming than walking.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_061_000	Under attack, it uses its belly spiral to put\nthe foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_062_000	Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its\nbody. It can even overtake world-class swimmers.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_063_000	Sleeps 18 hours a day. If it senses danger,\nit will teleport itself to safety even as it sleeps.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_064_000	Many odd things happen if this Pokémon is\nclose by. For example, it makes clocks\nrun backward.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_065_000	A Pokémon that can memorize anything.\nIt never forgets what it learns—that’s why\nthis Pokémon is smart.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_066_000	Very powerful in spite of its small size.\nIts mastery of many types of martial arts\nmakes it very tough.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_067_000	The belt around its waist holds back its energy.\nWithout it, this Pokémon would be unstoppable.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_068_000	One arm alone can move mountains.\nUsing all four arms, this Pokémon\nfires off awesome punches.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_069_000	Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares\ntiny bugs with its vines and devours them.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_070_000	When hungry, it swallows anything that moves.\nIts hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_071_000	Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey.\nSwallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day,\nbones and all.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_072_000	It can sometimes be found all dry and\nshriveled up on a beach. Toss it back\ninto the sea to revive it.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_073_000	Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely.\nThey wrap around prey and weaken it\nwith poison.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_074_000	Commonly found near mountain trails and\nthe like. If you step on one by accident,\nit gets angry.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_075_000	Often seen rolling down mountain trails.\nObstacles are just things to roll straight over,\nnot avoid.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_076_000	Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender\nand whitish. Its hide hardens when it’s\nexposed to air.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_077_000	Capable of jumping incredibly high.\nIts hooves and sturdy legs absorb\nthe impact of a hard landing.
ZKN_COMMENT_A_078_000	Just loves to run. If it sees something faster\nthan itself, it will give chase at top speed.
